We DO stand in the lines, but receive a return time so much of our wait time has been somewhere else (sitting down, using the restrooms, going to First Aid, etc). I hope you enjoy the video!

Sharon Quirk-Silva was interviewed outside of Disneyland today. She shared her thoughts about the Governors decision not to allow theme parks such as Disneyland to reopen until the county has reached the yellow tier. I wasn’t sure if my iPhone was picking up what she was saying so I tried to ensure I reiterated most of what she was saying. Disneyland is pushing hard to reopen. It’ll be interesting to see what happens as this is the first time in Disneyland history that the park has been shut down for such an extensive period of time.
.

node.text:
This is totally outside of the typical content I create and post, but I felt so strongly that this specific scene in the Netflix documentary Schitts Creek Best Wishes, Warmest Regards needed to be shared. Forgive me, you can hear me sniffling and crying as I filmed this. Schitts Creek is one of my favorite shows and has served as a super catalyst for acceptance, love, and positive personification of the LGBTQ+ community. I share some of my own thoughts and feelings (not very eloquently bc I had a hard time NOT crying) after the scene. I absolutely love that I am seeing more and more support LGBTQ+ community, but I also experience a devastating amount of hate on a daily basis. My goal behind our social media has been and will continue to be to offer ppl a small glimpse into our lives as a family in the hopes that we might open a few minds and hearts along the way. Love is love ❤️ And I hope and pray we see more and more queer representation in movies, television shows, books, etc. 🏳️‍🌈✊🏽 @schittscreek @instadanjlevy @annefrances 
.
.

HAPPY 6th BIRTHDAY TO MY SELF PROCLAIMED GIRLBOY 🥳 My sweet second born who came to me weighing 4 pounds and suffering from drug withdrawals. He’s the most high maintenance person I have ever met 😂 and def someone who knows what he wants. He’s my little shadow and my best buddy. There’s no one else like him in the entire world and I am so honored to be his mommy 😭

Evan, you’re changing the world and you don’t even know it. You live your life by your own rules and I wish I could be more like you. I’m so sorry you’ve had to see mommy cry so much this week, but I hope all the fun events have helped make you smile 😊 I love you to infinity and beyond and can’t wait to see all the amazing things you’ll do in your sweet life. Never stop being YOU!

#ad If you're like us you have a heart and a passion for rescue dogs. I adopted Ariel 3 years ago. She was picked up from a shelter by a rescue organization that saw her sad eyes and knew she needed a loving family.
​​​​​​
The Ariel you see in pictures and videos today is a completely different dog than when she came to us. She was malnourished and struggled with digestive issues related to her anxiety. The transition from shelter to rescue to home was a tough one for her. Finding the right kind of food to ease her stomach issues, provide her with the nutrients she needed, AND taste good felt like an impossible task.
​​​​​​
I can't tell you how much I wish ACANA Rescue Care for Adopted Dogs was available when I brought Ariel home. It was developed specifically for rescue dogs! ACANA created a food that not only supports your new pups immune system, but also helps with digestion. ACANA Rescue Care for Adopted Dogs can help make welcoming your new family member home a positive experience for you and your sweet pup! Now you won't have to stand in the dog food aisle the same way I did wondering if you're making the right choice or not. ACANA took the stress out of choosing a dog food for your rescue dog!
​​​​​​
